modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and generating HTTP/1.1 messages, handling headers, and managing request-response cycles. Works with byte sequences, strings, and custom data types representing HTTP methods, status codes, and headers. Used to build lightweight HTTP servers and clients with asynchronous I/O support.

Parses HTTP headers, requests, chunk lengths, and chunks from a bigstring, returning parsed data and an offset. Works with Cohttp's header and request types, as well as bigstrings for efficient buffer handling. Used to process incoming HTTP data in streaming scenarios, such as parsing request headers from a network buffer or extracting chunked content.
